# Form

`TxForm` provides the validation context for form fields. `TxFormItem` registers itself with the nearest form, resolves field rules, renders the label/message layout, and exposes field-level validation through the parent form instance.

Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/form/src/types.ts`, `TxForm.vue`, `TxFormItem.vue`, `context.ts`, and `form.test.ts`.

## Basic Usage

:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="FormFormDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { computed, reactive, ref } from 'vue'

  const formRef = ref()
  const form = reactive({ name: '', email: '' })
  const rules = computed(() => ({
    name: { required: true, message: 'Please enter your name' },
    email: {
      validator: (value: string) => {
        if (!value) return 'Please enter your email'
        return value.includes('@') || 'Invalid email format'
      },
    },
  }))

  async function submit() {
    const ok = await formRef.value?.validate()
    if (!ok) return
    // submit form
  }
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxForm ref="formRef" :model="form" :rules="rules" label-width="90px">
      <TxFormItem label="Name" prop="name">
        <TuffInput v-model="form.name" placeholder="Enter your name" />
      </TxFormItem>
      <TxFormItem label="Email" prop="email">
        <TuffInput v-model="form.email" placeholder="name@example.com" />
      </TxFormItem>
      <TxButton variant="primary" @click="submit">Validate</TxButton>
    </TxForm>
  </template>
---
:::

## Interaction Contract

- `TxForm` renders a native `<form>` and prevents default submit behavior.
- `TxFormItem` registers on mount and unregisters before unmount, so parent `validate()`, `resetFields()`, and `clearValidate()` only affect live fields.
- Form-level rules are looked up by `prop`; item-level `rules` override the form-level rule for the same field.
- Required validation treats `null`, `undefined`, `''`, and empty arrays as empty.
- A custom validator may return `true`, `false`, an error string, or a Promise of those values.
- `resetFields()` restores each registered field to its mounted initial value and clears its validation message.
- `required` on `TxFormItem` controls the required visual marker and augments validation when a rule is present. Use a required rule when the field must fail validation on empty input.
- `disabled` and `size` are provided through form context for descendants; slotted controls should still receive their own disabled/size props when the input component requires them.

## API

### TxForm Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `model` | `Record<string, any>` | - | Reactive form data object. `TxFormItem` reads fields by `prop`. |
| `rules` | `FormRules` | - | Form-level validation rules keyed by field prop. |
| `labelPosition` | `'left' \| 'right' \| 'top'` | `'left'` | Label layout used by child form items. |
| `labelWidth` | `string \| number` | - | Label width for non-top label layouts. Numbers become pixel values. |
| `size` | `'small' \| 'medium' \| 'large'` | `'medium'` | Form size exposed through context. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disabled state exposed through context. |

### TxForm Events

| Event | Payload | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `validate` | `(valid: boolean)` | Emitted after parent `validate()` resolves all registered items. |

### TxForm Expose

| Method | Signature | Description |
|------|-----------|-------------|
| `validate` | `() => Promise<boolean>` | Runs validation on every registered item and returns whether all passed. |
| `resetFields` | `() => void` | Restores mounted initial values for every registered item and clears messages. |
| `clearValidate` | `() => void` | Clears validation messages without changing model values. |

### TxFormItem Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `label` | `string` | `''` | Label text. Falls back to `prop` when omitted. |
| `prop` | `string` | - | Field key in the parent `model` and `rules`. |
| `rules` | `FormRule \| FormRule[]` | - | Item-level validation rules. Overrides form-level rules for this item. |
| `required` | `boolean` | `false` | Shows the required marker and augments required checks when a rule runs. |
| `showMessage` | `boolean` | `true` | Renders the validation error message below the field. |
| `inline` | `boolean` | `false` | Aligns label/content for compact inline rows. |

### TxFormItem Events

| Event | Payload | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `validate` | `(valid: boolean)` | Emitted after the item validates. |

### FormRule

| Field | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `required` | `boolean` | Enables empty-value validation. |
| `message` | `string` | Error message for required or `false` validator results. |
| `validator` | `(value, rule, model) => boolean \| string \| Promise<boolean \| string>` | Custom validator. Returning a string uses that string as the error message. |

### Slots

| Component | Slot | Props | Description |
|-----------|------|------|-------------|
| `TxForm` | `default` | - | Form item and action content. |
| `TxFormItem` | `default` | - | Field control content. |

## Best Practices

- Keep `model` stable and reactive; replacing it after mount can make reset semantics surprising.
- Prefer form-level `rules` for shared validation and item-level `rules` only for one-off overrides.
- Put async availability checks in `validator`, and return a string for the precise user-facing error.
- Pass `disabled` to both `TxForm` and the slotted controls when the whole form is locked.
- Call `clearValidate()` when switching between records without resetting user-entered values.

## Review Notes

- **Accessibility note:** `TxFormItem` renders a visible `<label>` but does not bind `for`/`id` automatically; ensure slotted controls receive matching IDs or explicit ARIA labels when the native label association matters.
- **Verified coverage:** `form.test.ts` exercises required-rule validation, error message rendering, successful revalidation after model updates, and `resetFields()` restoring the mounted initial value.

